definitions.definition: Any plant of the labiate genus Thymus , such as garden thyme ( Thymus vulgaris ), a warm, pungent aromatic, that is much used to give a relish to seasoning and soups.

main_definition: Any plant of the labiate genus Thymus , such as garden thyme ( Thymus vulgaris ), a warm, pungent aromatic, that is much used to give a relish to seasoning and soups.
